What you will learn:

Creating Single Page Applications with ojModule and oj.router

How to use this sample:

1. Open the sample.

2. Add 'header' and 'footer' modules and add in index.html:

<header data-bind="ojModule: {name:'header'}"></header>

<footer data-bind="ojModule: {name:'footer'}"></footer>

3. Add router.

In index.html, add router configuration between the header and footer:

<div id="mainContainer" data-bind="ojModule: router.moduleConfig"></div>

In main.js, load the router in the 'require' block:

'ojs/ojrouter'

In main.js, add router definition:

var router = oj.Router.rootInstance;
router.configure({
    'home': {label: 'Home', value: 'home', isDefault: true},
    'people': {label: 'People', value: 'people'}
});

Add the two modules 'home' and 'people'. 

4. Add navigation component.